##Housing enterprises to resume work later, developers to deal with the emergency way

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. The following article is from Caijing 11, by Wang Bo

Set up by the Industry Reporting Team of Caijing magazine to study the success and failure of enterprises, explore the rise and fall of industries, and promote sunshine business

Executives generally believe that adjusting the tax and purchase restrictions is an immediate help

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Wang Bo, Caijing reporter, and Mingjun Guo, intern

Editor | Marc

February 9, part of the head of housing enterprises again extended the resumption of work time, as of press release, Zhengrong, SUNAC, Longhu District, Ben Giang and other housing enterprises will be postponed to February 17.

Affected by the epidemic, the real estate industry into a super-long holiday. The Land Auction, the development, the marketing link link link rhythm slows down, the Housing Enterprise Fund backflow suddenly slow. Huatai Securities, a previous statistics show that the second half of 2020 real estate enterprises will enter a debt repayment peak, each quarter of the debt service (domestic debt) will exceed 120 billion yuan.

Housing enterprises in the fragile financial chain in the outbreak of the test.

Ping an securities, Minsheng Securities and other securities firms believe that the future financing conditions for enterprises to relax is a probability event.

But relaxed financing conditions will not solve the short-term crisis, housing executives generally believe that the most immediate positive measure or tax and purchase restrictions policy adjustments.

"The whole industry needs six months. "

Lee Ho is a salesman for SUNAC in Jiangsu Province. He told Caijing that the company did not specify when the sales staff would return to work, with an estimated date of Feb. 17. Now although can look at the House online, but customers are afraid of the epidemic will affect the price, wait-and-see in the majority. Not only that, many of the construction sites in the area where Lee Ho worked did not resume work.

"there are only a few ways for real estate companies to reduce their losses, except shouting slogans, such as live shoulder, or selling properties online, but buyers will surely wait and see, they are not optimistic about the future, and they have no confidence in the future, " a regional director of the China Communications Group told Caijing. CCCC announced that it would resume work on Feb. 10, but the executives could only do it online.

In contrast to the China Communications Group, Wanda executives have been meeting online since Feb. 2, and Wanda's grassroots workers are starting to work from home.

"Last year we finished early, we planned to start early this year, and now everything is in disarray, " said an executive at Wanda's Xi'an Business Management Company. As a result of the outbreak, Wanda's shopping malls across the country were basically closed, after the company announced that it would reduce the rent for all businesses for one month and property fees for Wanda Plaza, totaling about 4 billion yuan. The executive predicts the industry needs six months off.

Since late January 2020, turnover at most developers has plunged 95 per cent compared with previous Chinese New Year holidays, according to the Central Plain Property Research Centre. Real estate sales figures for the week before and after the Lunar New Year holiday are close to zero, and zero sales are expected to remain the norm for some time to come, Kerri said on a recent conference call.

The second-hand housing market is also not good, said Liu Feng, a manager in Beijing's Lianjia Dongcheng District. He said most of the Lianjia employees will return to Beijing on February 3, but will not open for work until the 10th. Now their customers are online VR house, but as of press time, there is not a single booking off-line house. "We have not issued a clear forecast, given the sudden outbreak, but as things stand, it should not be good for the next two months. "

Lianjia has already arranged a lot of internal learning and training for February-march, which Liu Feng believes shows that the company expects the number of customers to show up and the volume of transactions to be greatly reduced during this period.

Construction and land auctions were halted

After the resumption of the real estate industry, in addition to sales, construction and land has also been affected.

A Vanke, SUNAC and many other first-line real estate subcontractors told the "CAIJING" reporter, in previous years they required managers to be on the job before the 15th of the first month to prepare, about 80-90% of ordinary workers can be on the job. But this year the general contractor has not given a time to resume work, everyone is waiting for news. They now conduct daily online surveys of returning workers in preparation for their return to work. The main contents of the investigation are whether the body is normal, whether the workers can arrive at their posts in time after receiving the notification of resuming work, whether they come from key epidemic areas such as Hubei, whether the villages are in a closed state, whether the drivers can enter or leave, etc. .

"based on the survey data, the willingness of workers to return to work is strong, " said the subcontractor, who hopes the outbreak will turn around before the end of February.

At present, most provinces and cities have changed the resumption time to after the 15th day of the first lunar month or the end of February, and in previous years, construction site workers also work after the 15th day of the first lunar month.

But even if work resumes at the end of February, production will lag behind, because the workers will be isolated for 14 days when they return. The workshop may not be a big problem, but it will certainly be delayed due to the mix of workers on the site. "Our survey data shows that many of the villages where the key workers are located are closed and the arrival time can not be estimated and the government will intervene when they arrive, even if the developers are eager to meet the deadline, " the subcontractor said.

At present, many sites set for February 10, has been the normal start of about 10 days later. Evergrande, the company with the longest delay, has asked not to start work until February 20.

Regarding the resumption of work day, local governments have different requirements. On February 6, Nanjing announced that construction sites should resume work no earlier than 2400 hours on February 9, and encouraged enterprises to delay or stagger the resumption of work in the light of the epidemic situation and the actual situation on the site. Shenzhen requested that no earlier than February 10, but before the start of work to do a good job related records; Zhengzhou is the latest date to resume work, real estate projects until March 6 to resume work, sales department temporarily open.

An employee in Longhu District's finance department told Caijing that the government was also under pressure over revenues, both to start work as soon as possible and to avoid a large-scale resumption of work that could make the epidemic worse.

The above-mentioned subcontractors said that although the resumption date is not set, but they will not lay off workers, I believe that many large enterprises first thought of the way will not be laid off. "Most of the employees are skilled workers and it is not easy to produce them. It will be very difficult to hire people with similar skills after they are laid off. After all, there is a shortage of workers in China. "

Along with the construction sites is the land auction market.

"Can not go out, unless on-line auction. " The above-mentioned area of China Communications Group is always worried that many in 2019 holding high-turnover housing enterprises will "run out of food. ". In 2019 by the impact of financial regulation and cyclical regulation, many enterprises are in a tight money stage, only to maintain fast access to land, fast start, fast sales high turnover model, in order to maintain cash flow.

Although the pace of marketing, land buying and construction has slowed, affecting the cash flow of housing companies, bank interest and maturing debt must be paid on time or risk default and lower credit ratings, this will make the future financing cost of housing enterprises to further increase. If the epidemic situation is not effectively controlled, heavy warehouse epidemic areas of the more serious cash flow of housing enterprises will be tighter.

Although the pressure is big, but this round fights epidemic situation, the real estate business people actually react quickly, gallops the aid Hubei positively. At present, a total of 100 housing enterprises donated nearly 1.4 billion yuan, a number of real estate companies to set up epidemic funds, and to the epidemic areas donated masks, vegetables and other essential supplies.

Around the Spring Festival, a large number of shopping malls across the country closed, small and medium-sized shop owners goods backlog, heavy losses. Wanda, Jinmao, R & F, China Resources Real Estate, Rongchuang Wenlu group and other housing enterprises have announced the reduction of rent for all businesses, ranging from half a month to a month.

Whether the bank will relax credit standards, a number of real estate executives said, not yet, but there should be.

Vanke's two regional finance executives are hoping for changes in tax cuts, easier pre-sale conditions, mortgages and purchase restrictions, and more efficient administrative approvals. This, they argue, would do more to address short-term cash-flow problems than easing financing conditions.
